commit_message: add the python script that was used to create the supplemental figure showing the distribution of the CLAMT region in a wide selection of pearl millet accessions.

Merge branch 'bougous-master-patch-54402' into 'master'

Update 06.Post-Processing/plot_gene_length_bins_multi.py

See merge request bougous/millet-genome-annotation!3

This script can take multiple two column files to plot gene length versus count.

1. gene length counts data were generated using genometools gt stat 
gt stat -genelengthdistri -exonlengthdistri -exonnumberdistri -intronlengthdistri -cdslengthdistri -o P10K.hm.all+abinitio.r05+abinitio.newIDs.gff.stats P10K.hm.all+abinitio.r05+abinitio.newIDs.gff &
2. The gene lengths are binned into 1000 bins (can be changed) and counts accumulated per bin.
3. The gene lengths are converted to log10 values and plotted on the x-axis instead of the actual full length which could range from 0 to past 100kb.
